HEADWORD: Angelology
<hw>An`gel*ol"o*gy</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>angelus</ets>, Gr. <?/ + <ets>-logy</ets>.]</ety> <def>A discourse
on angels, or a body of doctrines in regard to angels.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The same mythology commanded the general consent; the same
<qex>angelology</qex>, demonology.</q> <rj><qau>Milman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

